\title{the [matrix](jms-00IS) associated to a finite [relation](jms-00I7)}
\date{2024-01-17}
\author{jonmsterling}
\taxon{definition}
\import{jms-00JB}

\p{Let #{R\colon\brk{m}\relto\brk{n}} be a [relation](jms-00I7); for any semiring #{S}, we may form the \dem{\nowrap{\prn{n\times n}-[matrix](jms-00I7)} over #{S} associated to #{R}} as follows:}

##{
 \prn{\matrix-of-rel_S{R}}_{i\in\brk{m},j\in\brk{n}} =
 \begin{cases}
   1&\text{if } i\mathrel{R}j
   \\
   0&\text{otherwise}
 \end{cases}
}

\p{We have defined a function #{\matrix-of-rel_S\colon \REL{\brk{m},\brk{n}} \to \MAT{S}{m}{n}}.}